The milk spike (S) glycoprotein binds to its cellular receptor angiotensin-converting enzyme 2 (ACE2) and the peptide-like peptide 4 (DPP4) from SARS-CoV and MERS-CoV respectively, and then the membrane fusion occurs.
The viral genes are released into the cytoplasm, then after the viral genes are copied, the genes make RNA-enveloped glycocarbons and nucleocycodonts, which then fuse with the plasma membrane to release the virus.
