On February 18, 2020, Bo Li Zheng and colleagues published a study comparing Western medicine (WM) treatment with Western medicine and traditional Chinese medicine.
They found that the recovery time, symptom relief, and hospital stay were abnormally short in the Western medicine + traditional Chinese medicine group compared to the Western medicine group alone.
Most impressively, the symptomatically increased (mild to severe) symptom was significantly lower in the WM+TCM group compared to the WM alone (7.4% versus 46.2%) and the mortality rate (8.8% versus 39%) was unusually low.
