Social distancing (also known as physical distancing) includes disease control actions that aim to reduce the spread of infection by limiting close contact between individuals.
These measures include quarantines, travel restrictions, and closures of schools, workplaces, stadiums, cinemas, or shopping centers.
People can implement social distancing practices by staying at home, avoiding going out in crowds, not receiving greetings, and staying physically distant from each other.
Many governments are enforcing or advising social distancing in areas affected by the pandemic.
